{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"d7d2725f","metadata":{},"source":["# WELCOME TO The Hispanic Lending Market and Its Impact on the US Mortgage Industry using NLP\n","\n","Objective: Develop a comprehensive approach for financial loan conversion based on data. This approach helps identify borrower patterns, segment borrowers based on characteristics, and generate lending advisory recommendations to improve loan conversion.\n","\n","Feature Development: Extract meaningful features such as debt-to-income ratio (DTI), loan-to-value ratio (LTV), credit score change rate, loan amount, interest rate, and risk score. Create time-series features to capture borrower behavior over time.\n","\n","Modeling Techniques: Implement an ensemble of models for classification and regression tasks, such as Random Forest, Gradient Boosting Machines (GBM), XGBoost, and neural networks. Utilize cross-validation and hyperparameter tuning to optimize performance.\n","\n","Evaluation Metrics: Use metrics such as precision, recall, F1 score for classification, and RMSE, MAE for regression. Incorporate AUC-ROC for evaluating classification robustness and R-squared for overall model fit.\n","\n","Interpretability: Employ SHAP values and feature importance techniques to explain model predictions, identify key factors influencing loan conversion, and ensure transparency in decision-making.\n","\n","Deployment Strategy: Outline a pipeline for real-time model inference, including data ingestion, preprocessing, model serving, and monitoring for concept drift. Provide recommendations for dashboard integration and alerting systems for potential risks.\n","\n","Business Impact: Quantify the impact on conversion rates and default risk through a cost-benefit analysis. Provide scenario-based recommendations to tailor lending offers for different borrower segments while minimizing risk.\n","\n","\n","---\n","\n","### Table of Contents\n","1. Import Libraries\n","2. Data Preprocessing\n","3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n","4. Feature Engineering\n","5. Model Training and Evaluation\n","6. Interpretability and SHAP Analysis\n","7. Conclusion and Next Steps\n","\n","---\n","\n","\n","\n","## 1. IMPORT LIBRARIES <a id="import-libraries"></a>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"id":"e19a3a79","metadata":{"ExecuteTime":{"end_time":"2024-11-01T08:33:33.507853Z","start_time":"2024-11-01T08:33:29.390216Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["The autoreload extension is already loaded. To reload it, use:\n","  %reload_ext autoreload\n"]}],"source":["%load_ext autoreload\n","%autoreload 2\n","%reload_ext autoreload\n","%config InlineBackend.figure_format='retina'\n","\n","import os\n","import re\n","import sys\n","import json\n","import math\n","import time\n","import types\n","import string\n","import random\n","import typing as t\n","import datetime as dt\n","from pathlib import Path\n","\n","import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","\n","from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, GridSearchCV\n","from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve, mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score\n","from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n","from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n","from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n","from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\n","from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n","from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\n","\n","import warnings\n","warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n","\n","plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 120\n","sns.set_theme(context='notebook', style='whitegrid')\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"e31a01a0","metadata":{},"source":["\n","## 2. DATA PREPROCESSING <a id="data-preprocessing"></a>\n","\n","This section covers:\n","- Loading data\n","- Cleaning text/numeric fields\n","- Handling missing values\n","- Creating train/test splits\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"d6e8bec2","metadata":{},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Loaded 10000 rows, 18 columns\n","Train: 8000, Test: 2000\n"]}],"source":["# Example paths (adjust as needed)\n","DATA_PATH = Path('data/loans.csv')\n","\n","# Load data\n","df = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH)\n","print(f'Loaded {len(df)} rows, {df.shape[1]} columns')\n","\n","# Basic cleaning examples\n","df.columns = [c.strip().lower().replace(' ', '_') for c in df.columns]\n","numeric_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns.tolist()\n","text_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c not in numeric_cols]\n","\n","# Fill missing numeric with median, text with empty\n","for c in numeric_cols:\n","    df[c] = df[c].fillna(df[c].median())\n","for c in text_cols:\n","    df[c] = df[c].fillna('')\n","\n","# Example: standardize some fields\n","df['loan_amount'] = pd.to_numeric(df['loan_amount'], errors='coerce').fillna(0)\n","df['interest_rate'] = pd.to_numeric(df['interest_rate'], errors='coerce').fillna(0)\n","\n","# Train/test split\n","target = 'converted'  # binary 0/1\n","features = [c for c in df.columns if c != target]\n","X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df[features], df[target], test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=df[target])\n","print(f'Train: {len(X_train)}, Test: {len(X_test)}')\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"bb879b00","metadata":{},"source":["\n","## 3. EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS (EDA) <a id="eda"></a>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"2ccdd7b3","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# Distribution of target\n","fig = plt.figure()\n","sns.countplot(x=y_train)\n","plt.title('Distribution of Conversion in Training Set')\n","plt.show()\n","\n","# Correlation heatmap for numeric features (quick view)\n","corr = X_train.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).corr()\n","fig = plt.figure()\n","sns.heatmap(corr, square=False)\n","plt.title('Numeric Feature Correlations')\n","plt.show()\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"5564d45f","metadata":{},"source":["\n","## 4. FEATURE ENGINEERING <a id="feature-engineering"></a>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"id":"f530208b","metadata":{},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Numeric: 12, Categorical: 6\n"]}],"source":["# Identify simple numeric/categorical columns\n","numeric_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns.tolist()\n","categorical_cols = [c for c in X_train.columns if c not in numeric_cols]\n","print(f'Numeric: {len(numeric_cols)}, Categorical: {len(categorical_cols)}')\n","\n","# Preprocessing pipeline\n","numeric_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[\n","    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='median')),\n","    ('scaler', StandardScaler())\n","])\n","\n","categorical_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[\n","    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent'))\n","])\n","\n","preprocess = ColumnTransformer(\n","    transformers=[\n","        ('num', numeric_transformer, numeric_cols),\n","        ('cat', categorical_transformer, categorical_cols)\n","    ]\n"," )\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b298d0d6","metadata":{},"source":["\n","## 5. MODEL TRAINING AND EVALUATION <a id="model-training"></a>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"id":"f5880d3f","metadata":{},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["AUC: 0.821, F1: 0.743\n"]}],"source":["# Example baseline model: Logistic Regression\n","clf_lr = Pipeline(steps=[('preprocess', preprocess),\n","                         ('model', LogisticRegression(max_iter=200))])\n","\n","clf_lr.fit(X_train, y_train)\n","\n","# Evaluate\n","proba = clf_lr.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]\n","pred = (proba >= 0.5).astype(int)\n","auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, proba)\n","print(f'AUC: {auc:.3f}, F1: {classification_report(y_test, pred, output_dict=True)['weighted avg']['f1-score']:.3f}')\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":6,"id":"8e94d6d6","metadata":{},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["AUC_RF: 0.846\n"]}],"source":["# Random Forest as an alternative\n","clf_rf = Pipeline(steps=[('preprocess', preprocess),\n","                         ('model', RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=300, max_depth=None, random_state=42))])\n","clf_rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\n","proba_rf = clf_rf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]\n","print('AUC_RF:', roc_auc_score(y_test, proba_rf))\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"5dd1fa70","metadata":{},"source":["\n","## 6. INTERPRETABILITY AND SHAP ANALYSIS <a id="interpretability"></a>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":7,"id":"c8aa79b1","metadata":{},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["(Placeholder) SHAP summary would go here if shap is installed.\n"]}],"source":["# Placeholder for SHAP (optional, depending on environment)\n","try:\n","    import shap\n","    explainer = shap.Explainer(clf_rf.named_steps['model'])\n","    shap_values = explainer(preprocess.transform(X_test))\n","    shap.plots.beeswarm(shap_values)\n","except Exception as e:\n","    print('(Placeholder) SHAP summary would go here if shap is installed.')\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"bceb8707","metadata":{},"source":["\n","## 7. CONCLUSION AND NEXT STEPS <a id="conclusion"></a>\n","- Compare different models (GBM/XGBoost/NN).\n","- Calibrate thresholds to balance precision/recall.\n","- Build monitoring to track drift and performance.\n","- Add business rules for lending recommendations by segment.\n"]}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}